 of German   Zehnder   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]},{"name":"Sant","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Krishan, Anagha, Anjali, Arvind, Deepak, Milind, Nilima, Ravindra, Sanjeev, Sanjiv, Vasudev.","English (Cheshire and Staffordshire): variant of   Saint  .","Italian (northeastern): variant of   Santo  ."]},{"name":"Sante","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Luc, Camille, Lucien.  Spanish Alejandro, Anselmo, Carlos, Emilio, Jesusa, Jorge.","French (also <b>Santé</b>): probably a nickname for a healthy person, from French <i>santé</i> ‘good health’.","Galician, Asturian-Leonese, and Spanish (southwestern): habitational name from one of several places called Sante, in Galicia, Portugal, and Asturias, from a Visigothic personal name. This surname is also found in the Philippines."]}]},{"name":"Evrard","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>Everard</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Evrard DE BERGHES SAINT WINOC-DE SELVESSE was born in 1158, in Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Elbodon Guy I de BERGHES SAINT WINOCK, was 25 and his mother, Dame Adele de Selvesse - Dame d'Ardres, was 18. He had at least 2 daughters with Gisèle de Rollancourt. He died in 1211, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1158–1211":"1158–1211","1168–1214":"1168–1214","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1189–1244":"1189–1244","1133–1188":"1133–1188","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1168":"1168","1189":"1189","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1188":"1188","1133":"1133","1187":"1187","1140":"1140","Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1158–1211":"1158–1211","1168–1214":"1168–1214","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1189–1244":"1189–1244","1133–1188":"1133–1188","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1168":"1168","1189":"1189","1211":"1211","1244":